---
import StarlightPage from '@astrojs/starlight/components/StarlightPage.astro';
import { Icon } from '@astrojs/starlight/components';
import { ImageExample } from '../../components/ImageExample';
import { Check } from 'lucide-react';
---

<StarlightPage 
  frontmatter={{ title: 'Getting Started' }}
  headings={[{
    depth: 2,
    slug:'javascript-api',
    text: 'JavaScript API'
  },{
    depth: 2,
    slug:'using-annotorious',
    text: 'Using Annotorious'
  }]}>

  <p>
    Annotorious is a JavaScript library for adding advanced image annotation 
    capabilities to your web application. Try it out below: <strong>click</strong> or 
    <strong>tap</strong> the annotation to edit, 
    <strong>click or tap anywhere and drag</strong> to create a new annotation.
  </p>

  <p>
    <ImageExample client:only="react" />
  </p>

  <p>
    Use the icons to <strong>switch between rectangle and polygon</strong> 
    drawing modes. When drawing a polygon, <strong>double click with your 
    mouse</strong> to close the shape, or <strong>keep your finger on the 
    screen and hold for a moment</strong> on a touch device.
  </p>

  <h2 id="javascript-api">JavaScript API</h2>

  <p>
    The Annotorious JavaScript API gives you programmatic control over 
    annotations, enables you to customize behavior and visual styling, and
    integrate Annotorious with the rest of your application. With the API, 
    you can:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>add, remove or update annotations programmatically,</li>
    <li>listen to user events,</li>
    <li>set filters,</li>
    <li>create data-driven styles, etc.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 id="using-annotorious">Using Annotorious</h3>

  <p>
    You can use Annotorious into your project in several ways, depending
    on your types of images and preferred JavaScript framework. 
  </p>
  
  <p>
    Annotorious supports <strong>standard images</strong> (JPEGs, PNGs, etc.) and 
    high-resolution <strong>zoomable images</strong> with the 
    <a href="https://openseadragon.github.io/" target="_blank">OpenSeadragon viewer</a>.
    It works with vanilla JavaScript, and provides bindings for <a href="https://react.dev/" target="_blank">React</a>.
    Bindings for <a href="https://svelte.dev/" target="_blank">Svelte</a> are currently in development.
  </p>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th></th>
        <th>
          <div>Images</div>
        </th>
        <th>
          <div>OpenSeadragon</div>
        </th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>
          <span><Icon name="seti:javascript" /> Vanilla JavaScript</span>
        </td>
        <td>
          <div><Check size={18} /></div>
        </td>
        <td>
          <div><Check size={18} /></div>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>
          <span><Icon name="seti:react" /> React</span>
        </td>
        <td>
          <div><Check size={18} /></div>
        </td>
        <td>
          <div><Check size={18} /></div>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>
          <span><Icon name="seti:svelte" /> Svelte</span>
        </td>
        <td>
          <div>incomplete</div>
        </td>
        <td>
          <div>incomplete</div>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</StarlightPage>

<style>
  table {
    padding-top: 2rem;
  }

  td > span {
    align-items: center;
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  td > div,
  th > div {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
  }
</style>


